6, 19 Why do I feel like I need to do that again? 13, 18 I've never felt that."" 6, 13 AS: That quickly. 5 MK: I was smoking weed, doing coke; I never woke up the next morning and wanted to do it again. 9, 10, 13, 14, 16, 19, 20 It would just be on weekends. 16 AS: Can I ask you a question? 15 Did you ever take pain pills for recreation use? 7, 9, 13, 20 MK: Nope.  AS: You went straight to injecting?  MK: I didn't inject.  I smoked.  I was doing uppers like cocaine. 10 I would smoke weed which kind of just puts you to sleep, other than that no pain pills. 19 AS: That wasn't your route into using heroin. 10 It was just...  MK: I was exposed to cocaine and then I was exposed to heroin which is uncommon. 10 Usually it is pain pills or like my parents had surgery or something or my grandma had surgery and I'm going to take their pain pills. 7, 12, 20 None of that. 12 I never was a pill popper or anything like that. 13 I never found that enjoyable. 11, 13, 18 When I started smoking heroin the next morning, it was barely even 12 hours after that. 6, 7, 9, 10, 12, 15, 16, 19 I was like, ""Oh my God I need to do this every day."" 9, 14, 19 I was working in Chaska and my boyfriend lived across the street. 7, 11, 13, 16, 20 I remember I would just call him every day at work, ""You need to come to the parking lot. 7, 13, 14, 15, 17, 19 Let's go for a cruise.""  Meaning that we're going to get high. 11, 20 ""I have a half hour lunch break. 7, 10, 16 We can just drive down the road."" 14 AS: You'd get high and come back to work? 11, 17, 19, 20 MK: I'd get high in the morning before I'd go to work. 9, 11, 20 I'd go to work for a few hours, have a lunch break and then get high in the parking lot of work. 7, 10, 11, 20 AS: And then after work probably? 12, 13 MK: Then after work of course.  What was your job?  MK: I was working at a call center, sitting there talking on the phone all day. 6, 7, 12, 14, 17, 18, 19 MK: It was called Heartland America in Chaska. 13, 14, 17 It was a ma