to sit down and have a conversation with them and ask them how they're doing and how their lives are. 6, 7, 11, 13, 15, 16, 18 I got to ask my grandma, ""What was your favorite memory of your life?"" 7, 8 And actually listening to what she had to say instead of going, ""Oh ok. 14, 18 I didn't really mean to ask that question."" 6, 7, 8, 15 AS: Or even that you would sit down. 7 MK: That I would even actually seem like I cared but I actually do genuinely care for people now these days. 5, 7, 14, 17, 18, 19, 20 It's easier for me now to take time out of my day just to talk to you rather than really not having anything else to do but just leaving the house and doing nothing. 6, 7, 8, 9, 11, 16, 17, 19, 20 AS: Just to leave.  MK: Right, just to say I'm doing something but I'm really not doing anything. 6, 7, 8, 14 I have genuine friends in my life now. 7, 8, 13, 17 My best friend who I live with in California she has a two and a half year old son and I'm trusted with him alone at the house. 6, 9, 11, 12, 13, 16, 17 I'm trusted driving with him and picking him up from school and dropping him off at school. 5, 6, 11, 18 He loves me as much as I love him. 17 I've never felt so much love for my best friend and her son in my whole entire life. 6, 7, 8, 13, 17 AS: That is so neat.  Did you meet her in treatment? 7, 13, 18 MK: No, funny story. 8, 13 She went to my high school out here in Minnesota. 11 She moved to Kentucky. 11, 14 She was friends with my ex-boyfriend but I had never met her before. 7, 12, 13, 16 She added me on Facebook and we kind of started chatting. 6, 15 She's been with me my whole journey of sobriety and even before that.  She knew me when...we would Facetime when I was getting high. 6, 7, 11, 12, 15, 16, 19, 20 At that time we had never met face to face. 7, 12, 13, 16, 19 When I moved out to Long Beach when I got into sober living she had moved out to California as well to her dad's house. 6, 8, 9, 11, 14 I come to find out her dad lived right around the