14, 17 I called a realtor the following morning. 7, 9, 13, 14, 17 I said, “Hey, I was watching this program last night and I was thinking about how to become a realtor.” 7, 8, 13, 14, 15, 17, 18, 19 He said, “Well, who am I talking to?” 6, 13, 14 I told him my name and he said, “My name is Mark Grossman. 11, 13, 14, 16 I’m with Iowa realty.” 7 We talked for a little bit and I said, “Yeah. 6, 13, 14, 20 I really want to do this.” 6, 7, 8, 14 He said, “You sound like you’ve got the gift of gab. 13, 14 Why don’t you come down to the office?” 17, 18 I went down and there and he told me I was hired. 7, 13, 16 He said, “I’ll put you through real estate school, you’ll get your license, and you can work for us. 7, 11, 13, 14, 17, 18, 19, 20 You will get this commission rate. 20 Every time you sell a house for one hundred thousand dollars you get three percent of any home you sell.” 7, 9, 11, 16, 17, 18, 19, 20 I was like, “Three percent. 9, 14 Are you kidding me? 15 Done! 12 I studied hard and I really applied myself. 6, 7, 8, 17 This was the first time that I moderated my alcohol, I moderated my marijuana use to very low amounts. 7, 9, 10, 12, 16, 19 A little weed here or there, but nothing to where I am losing continuity. 20 I am still plugged in. 7 I am learning. 5 I studied hard. 6, 17 I don’t know how many weeks this course was, but I had to take my boards and I got a ninety-eight. 16, 17, 18, 20 I got a ninety-eight.  I knew this stuff by the back of my hand. 6, 11, 12, 13, 17, 19 I was going to become a millionaire. 7, 17, 18 I started working for Iowa Realty and I slowly realized that it was not what I thought it was going to be. 6, 7, 10, 15 You sit in these open houses for a long time and you don’t have anyone that calls you and you have to make cold calls. 7, 9, 11, 14, 16, 17, 18, 19, 20 I met some people that were selling conventionally listed properties on contract. 9, 12, 19 Basically you take this conventionally listed property and you create a contract, sel