at that. 6, 7, 8, 9, 17, 19 I would take tickets from forty-five dollars to one hundred dollars really fast. 6, 7, 8, 18, 20 I wasn’t a bad looking young man. 6 Plus, I had this gift of gab.  I did really good work. 6, 7, 8, 19 When I’m working I work hard. 6 I would clean the carpets and I would show the lady in the house the carpets. 9, 11, 14, 15, 16 I would say, “I’ve got a quote for you in the other room.” 9, 14 AS: She’s got one clean room and four dirty rooms! 9, 15, 16 Because it was only forty-four dollars. 18 That’s right. 8, 14 By the time I’m leaving I’m collecting a check for three hundred and fifty buck and I’m making one hundred and something per house. 7, 9, 11, 16, 19 I’m making three to four hundred dollars per house. 9, 11, 18 I was thinking, I’m really good at this and I really like this, too. 6, 7, 8, 19 One day Jimmy comes up to me, the guy I was working with, and he says, “Here, take a couple of these.” 6, 7, 14, 17, 19, 20 He hands me a couple Vicodin. 7, 13 I said, “What the hell do I want them for?” 13, 14 He said, “Fine.” 13, 14 I was like, God, this reminds me of something. 6, 7, 9, 14 Then I was like, “Yeah, I want those. 9, 14 Let me try those.”  “Give me two!  I could probably do three. 12, 13 Give me two.”  I fell in love. 17 Vicodin was it for me.  AS: Every time you get a new drug you’re like, Oh, that’s the one. 6, 7, 9, 10, 12, 14, 16, 19, 20 I went to Jimmy and asked if I could get five or six more of those for the weekend. 16, 20 He said, “I don’t have anymore.” 7, 13, 14 I asked him where he got them and if he could hook me up. “ I can’t tell you where I got them.” 13 I was like, “Come on dude. 9, 14 All of a sudden now you’re Mr. Secret.” 7, 17 “If I tell you you can’t tell anyone.” 13 “Of course.”  “You get them from the bathrooms.” 9, 12, 20 “What are you talking about?” 6 “When you go to your customer’s house you ask them if you can use the restroom. 7, 9, 11 “In every house?” 9, 11 “Not in every house, but most of them.” 9