am not breathing. 7, 19 She gives me a few short rescue breaths and I start to shallow breath. 6, 7, 11 She gets out the stethoscope and starts to monitor my heart. 6, 14, 20 It isn’t normal it is very weak. 18 She breaths for me and she doesn’t call nine one one because there is dope in the house. 7, 9, 11, 14, 17 There is cocaine in the house, there are stolen pills in the house, there are scales in the house, marijuana, baggies. 9, 10, 11, 16 There is a whole shop set up downstairs.  To call the ambulance means that DHS comes in and takes the kids. 14, 15, 17, 20 They take me to jail, they take the children away, they take everything. 7, 9, 13, 20 She is literally the person that saved my life that night. 7, 8, 10, 17, 19 AS: She was able to stabilize you? 18 WL: She was able to stabilize me. 18 She gave me mouth to mouth. 18 She breathed for me and kept me alive. 7, 11 I fell asleep after I got to a point where I was stable and my breathing was normal. 7, 10, 11, 18, 19 She let me sleep.  I woke up at one thirty in the morning and I said, “Where the fuck is my chicken?” 9, 13, 14 I have really very little emotional response because I don’t remember any of that. 6, 7, 8, 13, 15, 20 AS: But she told you. 13, 16 WL: Yeah, several times in detail. 7, 13, 16, 19 [laughs] 10 After that you think a person would stay sober and stay clean, but I kept thinking, I’ve got this. 10, 14, 15, 16, 17 But I couldn’t because every time I would stop I would get sick. 7, 16, 19, 20 I would have to chew the pills in the morning to get them in my system faster. 9, 20 I would drink some kind of liquor with it because it would immediately hit my system and I would get in the hot shower all at the some time. 7, 9, 12, 16, 19, 20 I was in the shower, hanging my head, chewing Vicodin, with a shot of whiskey in me getting ready to start my day. 5, 6, 7, 9, 12, 15, 18, 19, 20 I would brush my teeth and go clean the carpet again. 14, 15, 16 At that time I was making probably two thousand to 