my arms up and down.  Sometimes I would use my calves at times to find spots. 7, 9, 10, 12, 16, 19 My neck at times. 7, 16, 19 The abscess is from dope not being able to metabolize in my body. 12, 18 In animal studies we call it intraperitoneal. 12, 14, 17 It is the blank cavity in the body, so the only place it would go was to settle in the groin area. 7, 8 You could literally brush a powder off of my leg like dried cocaine. 10 I was losing that leg, I could tell. 13 My toes were getting dark blue. 15, 20 My leg was getting black. 15, 20 I didn’t care. 7, 14, 20 I thought if I lose this leg I can get on disability. 10, 13, 20 If I get disability I will be able to do dope for the rest of my life until I am dead. 7, 8, 18, 20 A lot of paranoid schizophrenia stuff with the cocaine. 7, 10 I would hunker down in the basement.  I almost shot my wife one night as she was walking downstairs. 6, 12, 15, 19, 20 AS: You almost shot her? 15, 20 WL: I had a shotgun pointed at her head. 10, 12, 20 I used to rig stuff up at the top of the stairs. 9 I would put a beer bottle on the door knob so that if someone would come in it would fall down the steps and I would hear it. 11, 12, 14, 16, 17, 19, 20 I always had a loaded shot gun next to me because if the cops came I was not going to jail. 10, 13, 16, 17, 19, 20 AS: You were going to shoot yourself?  WL: Yes.  Like I said, I don’t do time. 7, 13, 14, 16, 19 I won’t do time. 7, 16, 19 I was locked inside my mind for a long time as a kid. 6, 7, 15, 16, 19 AS: You were locked in your room. 9 WL: I never thought of that. 10, 13 That’s got some emotion there.  AS: It is fresh in my head so it is easy for me to make those connections when I’m listening. 7, 11, 12, 18 WL: Goddamn, you’re right. 7, 8, 14 AS: When somebody says, “I don’t do that,” well, what if someone told you you had to? 8, 13, 14, 16, 17 WL: I would kill myself.  AS: Right.  I couldn’t have asked you that thirty minutes ago. 14, 16 I ended up going to treatment. 7, 13, 