some ridiculous talent in Chicago at the time. 7, 15, 16, 19 Amy Poehler was one of my classmates. 6, 12 AS: Were you at Second City?  MO: Yes, I was a student at Second City. 11 Steve Carrell was one of my teachers. 7 I used to watch Stephen Colbert on a pretty much nightly basis. 5, 7, 9, 14, 15, 19 He was a remarkable talent, not entirely brilliant but he was just so brave. 7, 18 I'd just watch a person fail, and fail, and fail, and fail and then take off like a bird. 10, 15, 17, 20 That's a rare thing. 7, 19 Tina  Fey was just about a year behind me in the classes. 6, 12, 16 It was an awesome group of talented people that it was great to be around, thrilling to be around. 7, 8, 18 Artistic people and people who really gave a damn, social activism that I didn't grow up around in the very white Orange County, California. 6, 7, 8, 15, 18, 19 I met my former wife in Chicago. 12, 16 We got married and knew we weren't going to stay in Chicago because we'd end up out in the 'burbs and we didn't want to. 6, 12, 14, 16 We moved back to Minnesota where she is from and I really liked Minnesota. 6, 7, 8, 9, 11, 14, 17, 19 In '97 we had a son. 17 My son Devin was born. 5, 17 It was just everything I've always wanted. 10, 14 I've grown up around tons of children, nieces and nephews, and I've always enjoyed children but I knew I wasn't a very mature young adult. 6, 7, 9, 10, 12 I didn't want to get married or have kids when I was young. 6, 12, 14, 15, 16, 20 Here I was at thirty-four and I had my first child. 9, 16 He was just delightful.  He was just a lovely little guy. 6, 17, 20 I was just madly in love with him, we did so much stuff together. 11, 16, 17, 20 His mom was way more into labelling. 17 ""He's a spirited child."" 9 He's just a kid you know. 15, 17 He got along with everybody. 7, 15 Every kid liked Devin. 9, 14, 15 He just followed along. 7, 15 All through school every review of teachers was, ""I wish I had ten Devins in every class."" 6, 7, 11, 12 That being said