and my mom wake me up and they say, ""We're going to the hospital."" 8, 11, 14, 17, 19 And I... I was just out of it.  It doesn't even occur to me that this is unusual.  I just put my clothes on, like, ""Okay, we're going to the hospital."" 8, 9, 14, 19 I wasn't going to talk to them or ask them questions. 6, 15 [laughter]. 9 So I get in the car and we drive, Stewartville is just south of Rochester. 14, 20 We drive to Rochester, thinking we're going to Mayo, that's where we always get our healthcare, but we don't. 7, 10, 14, 20 We go pick my dad up at IBM. 5 And then, we go north towards the Twin Cities.  And that's just weird.  AS: And you’re like, what’s going on? 7, 9, 14 MS: Well no, not really. 6, 7, 8 I am in this debilitated state. 17 Just kind of intoxicated and wiped out.  I learned later that the minister was right behind me in the car, thinking that if I jumped out, they would be able to grab me. 5, 8, 14, 16, 18 Which at the time, hadn't even crossed my mind. 6, 7, 16, 19 I'm not even thinking, let alone acting. 12 So, we get to Minneapolis/St. 20 Paul and I'm thinking, ""I wonder why we are going to a hospital in the Twin Cities."" 8 Those are the only thoughts I'm having. 10 Yeah, I was not thinking clearly or much. 6 Then we get passed the Twin Cities and that's when I got really frightened. 6, 7, 8, 9, 14, 17 Because in my understanding of what was going on with me, I just thought I was going crazy. 10, 17 That was my high school understanding of my behavior. 11, 17 I am just going crazy and that they finally figured it out. 7, 19 And now they are taking me to a sanitarium in the North Woods. 17 AS: Oh right, you think you’re going to a mental hospital? 7, 8, 14 MS: Right, yeah. 8 I don't know what it is. 17 I've never been to one, but I am just assuming that must be what they do with people like me. 13 But they kind of did!  They brought me here! 20 [laughter] 9 Not really, but you know. 6, 7, 8, 17 AS: No, but in your mind—yeah, what is this place?